npc/yani: The portal ahead takes you to Stage 3 — the Cyber Network, where the money actually moves.
npc/yani: Remember what Eko showed you: the house edge decided the ending before you ever pressed spin. You cannot win back what the math has already taken.
npc/yani: So the people who keep trying don't climb out. They fall — deeper into debt. That's the next layer, and it's what you'll see there.
npc/yani: You'll meet Firewall Sentinels down there — the system's immune response. They don't care about right or wrong, only about protecting the structure.
npc/yani: And something worse. The system calls her the Collector. We called her the Witch — debt enforcement, built to chase people who borrowed to keep gambling and could not pay.
npc/yani: She remembers every name the algorithm ever marked as a debtor. If she finds you in there, she will not let go easily.
npc/yani: One thing before you go — that gate behind me. I'm opening it myself. No key to climb for, no "one more win" to earn it. You just had to stop and talk to someone.
npc/yani: And take this. The layer ahead will drop you, over and over — everyone falls down there.
npc/yani: The trick isn't never falling. It's catching yourself halfway down: jump again in mid-air and pull yourself back up.
npc/yani: A second chance. You always have one — as long as you choose to use it. That's the difference between slipping and falling for good.
npc/yani: Go. Don't stop now.
